{
  "doc_id": "10149",
  "text": "In [CITATION_1] , forming the independence complex of a graph is generalized to arbitrary simplicial complexes. For a simplicial complex K, define I(K) by declaring the facets of K to be the minimal non-faces of I(K). (The independent set complex in [CITATION_2] is defined in greater generality, allowing for K to be a set system which is not necessarily a simplicial complex.)",
